	<Title>
		Stop your next migraine before it starts
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Medication is a proven way to treat and prevent migraines, but medication is only part of the story. Healthy habits can sometimes stop migraine pain before it starts: 1. Establish regular sleep hours. Take time to unwind at the end of the day. If you can&apos;t fall asleep, read or do another quiet activity until you become drowsy. 2. Eat at about the same time every day. Don&apos;t skip meals. Avoid foods that seem to trigger migraines. 3. Exercise regularly. 4. Keep stress under control.&lt;/p&gt;
